1 - Please setup nginx 

2 - run command : 
sudo apt update

3 - run command : 
sudo apt install mariadb-server

4 - check status / run command : 
sudo systemctl status mariadb

5 - check version / run command : 
sudo systemctl status mariadb

6 - setup security / run command : 
sudo mysql_secure_installation

______________________________________

7 - Connect Console Mysql : 
 mysql -u root -p
 
 
8 - Run Command : 
Show Databases 


9 - Run Command : 
Use {namaTable};

10 - Run Command : 
Show tables; 

11 - Create databases / Run Command :

CREATE TABLE Persons (
    ID int NOT NULL,
    LastName varchar(255) NOT NULL,
    FirstName varchar(255),
    Age int,
    PRIMARY KEY (ID)
);


12 - Test Run / Run Command : 
select * from {namaTable};


13 - Check columns / Run Command : 
DESCRIBE {namaTable};


